{"questionId":"11756","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Urvashi wants to model the height of a moving object. She collects the following data showing the height, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"h\">\n  <mi>h</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp; metres, of the object at time <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> seconds.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/1b8ea3fd216ff6ca44f745b8e6644c5d437f1dbc.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">She believes the height can be modeled by a quadratic function,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"h\\left( t \\right) = a{t^2} + bt + c\">\n  <mi>h</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a{\\text{,}}\\,\\,b{\\text{,}}\\,\\,c \\in \\mathbb{R}\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4a + 2b + c = 34\">\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>34</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t = 2{\\text{,}}\\,\\,h = 34 \\Rightarrow \\,\\,34 = a{2^2} + 2b + c\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>h</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>34</mn>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mn>34</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1 </strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow {\\text{ }}34 = 4a + 2b + c\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>&nbsp;</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mn>34</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11756","referenceCode":"EXM.2.SL.TZ0.3a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that 4 a + 2 b + c = 34 .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}